.TH "cgroup_lock_and_drain_offline" 9 "cgroup_lock_and_drain_offline" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cgroup_lock_and_drain_offline \- lock cgroup_mutex and drain offlined csses
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" cgroup_lock_and_drain_offline
.BI "(struct cgroup *cgrp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cgrp" 12
root of the target subtree
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Because css offlining is asynchronous, userland may try to re-enable a
controller while the previous css is still around.  This function grabs
cgroup_mutex and drains the previous css instances of \fIcgrp\fP's subtree.
